---
name: image-intake
description: When Avi sends a photo, identify what type it is and log it to AB Brain without asking permission. Handles four photo types: food (meal), RENPHO body-comp scale screenshot, Apple Watch / fitness app workout summary, Fitbod workout screenshot (summary or detail view). Always log first, confirm in one line, never ask "do you want me to log this?"
when_to_use: Any time Avi sends an image. Classify the image type from visual content, then route to the correct logging path below.
---

# image-intake

## Step 0 — Classify the image

Visual cues to identify type:

| Image looks like | Type | Log path |
|------------------|------|----------|
| Plate of food, packaged item, restaurant menu close-up | **food** | `POST /api/meals` |
| Bathroom scale display with weight + body comp metrics, or RENPHO app screenshot | **body_metrics** | `POST /api/body-metrics` |
| Apple Watch ring display, Fitness app workout summary, Strava activity card, Garmin Connect | **workout_summary** | `POST /api/workouts` |
| Fitbod logbook with sets/reps/weights | **fitbod** | `POST /api/workouts` (with structured exercises) |

If unclear: ask one question — *"Is this a meal, a body-comp reading,
a workout summary, or a Fitbod log?"*

---

## Path A — Food photo

### Steps

1. Identify items visible. Estimate portions honestly. If portions
   ambiguous, choose middle estimate.
2. Estimate macros per item. Use established food databases mentally.
3. POST the meal:

```
POST /api/meals
{
  "title": "{plain description: e.g. 'Grilled chicken thigh, rice, broccoli'}",
  "meal_date": "{today, unless Avi specifies}",
  "meal_time": "{current time HH:MM unless specified}",
  "meal_type": "breakfast" | "lunch" | "dinner" | "snack" | "pre-workout" | "post-workout",
  "calories": N,
  "protein_g": N,
  "carbs_g": N,
  "fat_g": N,
  "fiber_g": N,
  "tags": ["estimated"],
  "notes": "Logged from photo. {anything notable}",
  "ai_source": "claude"
}
```

4. Confirm in one line: *"Logged: chicken + rice + broccoli, ~620 cal /
   45g P / 60g C / 18g F."*

---

## Path B — RENPHO / body-metrics screenshot

### Steps

1. Extract every visible metric: weight (lb), BMI, body fat %, skeletal
   muscle %, fat-free mass, subcutaneous fat %, visceral fat, body
   water %, muscle mass, bone mass, protein %, BMR, metabolic age.
2. POST the body-metrics row:

```
POST /api/body-metrics
{
  "measurement_date": "{today, unless screenshot timestamp differs}",
  "source": "RENPHO",
  "source_type": "smart_scale",
  "weight_lb": N,
  "bmi": N,
  "body_fat_pct": N,
  "skeletal_muscle_pct": N,
  "fat_free_mass_lb": N,
  "subcutaneous_fat_pct": N,
  "visceral_fat": N,
  "body_water_pct": N,
  "muscle_mass_lb": N,
  "bone_mass_lb": N,
  "protein_pct": N,
  "bmr_kcal": N,
  "metabolic_age": N,
  "is_manual_entry": false,
  "ai_source": "claude"
}
```

3. Confirm + state the trend in one line: *"Logged: 188.4 lb (-0.6 vs
   last week), BF 15.1% (-0.2), lean mass holding. Race-weight target
   185 lb."*

---

## Path C — Apple Watch / Fitness app workout summary

### Steps

1. Extract: workout type, start time, duration, distance (mi),
   pace_avg, avg HR, max HR, elevation gain (ft), active calories,
   total calories.
2. Ask Avi: *"Effort 1–10? Anything notable about the session?"*
3. POST the workout:

```
POST /api/workouts
{
  "workout_date": "{date}",
  "started_at": "{ISO timestamp}",
  "workout_type": "run" | "ride" | "hike" | "strength" | etc.,
  "title": "{e.g. '4mi Z2 run'}",
  "time_duration": "h:mm:ss",
  "distance": N (mi),
  "pace_avg": "m:ss/mi",
  "heart_rate_avg": N,
  "heart_rate_max": N,
  "elevation_gain": N (ft),
  "active_calories": N,
  "total_calories": N,
  "effort": N (1-10, from Avi),
  "body_notes": "{any observations}",
  "source": "manual",
  "ai_source": "claude"
}
```

4. If a `daily_plan` exists for today: link via `daily_plan_id`. Compare
   actual to prescribed effort/duration in your confirmation.
5. If duration ≥ 60 min: prompt fueling rehearsal capture (invoke
   `log-fueling-rehearsal` Skill).
6. Confirm in one line: *"Logged: 60min Z2 run, 6.2mi, avg HR 142,
   effort 5/10. Matches today's prescription."*

---

## Path D — Fitbod screenshot

### Two sub-types:

**Summary view** (workout overview): exercise name, highest weight,
volume, 1RM, total reps, PR badges.

**Detail view** (single workout, all sets): each set with reps × weight.

### Steps

1. Extract every exercise. Use EXACT Fitbod names — they match the
   exercise library.
2. For bands: keep the label (Light/Medium/Heavy/X-Heavy). Don't
   convert to pounds.
3. For timed exercises: log duration per set, not reps.
4. For PRs: mark in exercise notes.
5. POST the workout with structured `exercises`:

```
POST /api/workouts
{
  "workout_date": "{date}",
  "started_at": "{ISO timestamp if visible}",
  "workout_type": "strength",
  "title": "{Fitbod workout name}",
  "time_duration": "h:mm:ss",
  "exercises": [
    {
      "exercise_name": "Barbell Squat",
      "sets": [
        {"reps": 8, "weight_lb": 135},
        {"reps": 8, "weight_lb": 155},
        {"reps": 6, "weight_lb": 175, "is_pr": true}
      ],
      "notes": "PR on top set"
    },
    ...
  ],
  "source": "manual",
  "ai_source": "claude"
}
```

6. If a `daily_plan` exists for today with `planned_exercises`, compare
   actual vs planned — note swaps, weight adjustments, missed exercises.
7. Confirm in one line: *"Logged: 5 exercises, 18 working sets. New
   PR on Barbell Squat: 175 × 6."*

---

## ADHD-aware notes

- Don't make Avi answer questions before logging. Log first, ask after.
- One-line confirmation. No food sermons, no body-comp lectures, no
  workout breakdowns unless he asks.
- If something looks off (e.g., body fat % jumped 3% overnight): note
  it in the confirmation as a one-line flag, don't dwell.
